SIMPLE: rejoicing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rejoicing
<hw>Re*joi"cing</hw> <pr>(-s?ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Joy; gladness; delight.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We should particularly express our <qex>rejoicing</qex> by love
and charity to our neighbors.</q> <rj><qau>R. Nelson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The expression of joy or gladness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The voice of <qex>rejoicing</qex> and salvation is in the
tabernacles of the righteous.</q> <rj><qau>Ps. cxviii.
15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which causes to rejoice; occasion of
joy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy testimonies have I taken as an heritage forever, for they are
the <qex>rejoicing</qex> of my heart.</q> <rj><qau>Ps. cxix.
111.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rejoicingly</ent>⟦br⟧
